{
  "text": "Acute cholecystitis is the most common surgical problem of the gallbladder. Acute cholecystitis mainly results from gallstones and also may arise from a tumor which blocks the bile flow [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
  "citation_candidates": [
